The President and First Lady issued a statement on the first anniversary of Nelson Mandela's passing. They expressed their thoughts and prayers for the Mandela family and all South Africans. They highlighted Mandela's leadership, struggle, and sacrifices, which inspired people to stand up for fundamental principles and emphasized the need for compassion, understanding, and reconciliation. They also mentioned Mandela's vision for a better world and encouraged everyone to reflect on how his life has inspired them. The statement acknowledged the progress made but also emphasized the need for continued work. They concluded by honoring Mandela's spirit and memory.